  "id": "api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat",
  "title": "getLocaleDateTimeFormat",
  "contents": "\n\n<article>\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts?message=docs(common)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L283-L313\" aria-label=\"建议修改\" title=\"建议修改\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.1.0/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts#L283-L313\" aria-label=\"查看源码\" title=\"查看源码\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n</div>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n        \"itemListElement\": [\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.cn//api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.cn/api/common\", \"name\": \"@angular/common\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.cn/api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat\", \"name\": \"getLocaleDateTimeFormat\" } }\n        ]\n      }\n    </script>\n      <a href=\"/api\">API</a> / <a href=\"api/common\">@angular/common</a>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"getlocaledatetimeformat\">getLocaleDateTimeFormat<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat#getlocaledatetimeformat\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label function\">function</label>\n    \n    <label class=\"api-status-label experimental\">试验性的</label>\n    \n    \n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n    \n  <p class=\"short-description\"></p><p translation-origin=\"off\">Date-time format that depends on the locale.</p>\n<p></p>\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n  \n\n<code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" linenums=\"false\" class=\"no-box api-heading\"> <a href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat\" class=\"code-anchor\">getLocaleDateTimeFormat</a>(<a href=\"api/common/NgLocaleLocalization#locale\" class=\"code-anchor\">locale</a>: string, width: <a href=\"api/common/FormatWidth\" class=\"code-anchor\">FormatWidth</a>): string</code-example>\n\n<h4 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"参数\">参数</h4>\n<table class=\"is-full-width list-table parameters-table function-overload-parameters\">\n  <tbody>\n  \n    <tr class=\"function-overload-parameter\">\n      <td class=\"param-name\"><a id=\"\"></a>locale</td>\n      \n      <td class=\"param-description\">\n            <p translation-origin=\"off\">Type: <code>string</code>.</p>\n      \n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr class=\"function-overload-parameter\">\n      <td class=\"param-name\"><a id=\"\"></a>width</td>\n      \n      <td class=\"param-description\">\n            <p translation-origin=\"off\">Type: <code><a href=\"api/common/FormatWidth\" class=\"code-anchor\">FormatWidth</a></code>.</p>\n      \n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n<h4 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"返回值\">返回值</h4>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>string</code></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n  \n\n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">说明<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p translation-origin=\"off\">The date-time pattern shows how to combine separate patterns for date (represented by {1})\nand time (represented by {0}) into a single pattern. It usually doesn't need to be changed.\nWhat you want to pay attention to are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>possibly removing a space for languages that don't use it, such as many East Asian languages</li>\n<li>possibly adding a comma, other punctuation, or a combining word</li>\n</ul>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">For example:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>English uses <code>{1} 'at' {0}</code> or <code>{1}, {0}</code> (depending on date style), while Japanese uses\n<code>{1}{0}</code>.</li>\n<li>An English formatted date-time using the combining pattern <code>{1}, {0}</code> could be\n<code>Dec 10, 2010, 3:59:49 PM</code>. Notice the comma and space between the date portion and the time\nportion.</li>\n</ul>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">There are four formats (<code><a href=\"api/core/Version#full\" class=\"code-anchor\">full</a></code>, <code>long</code>, <code>medium</code>, <code>short</code>); the determination of which to use\nis normally based on the date style. For example, if the date has a full month and weekday\nname, the full combining pattern will be used to combine that with a time. If the date has\nnumeric month, the short version of the combining pattern will be used to combine that with a\ntime. English uses <code>{1} 'at' {0}</code> for full and long styles, and <code>{1}, {0}</code> for medium and short\nstyles.</p>\n\n</section>\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n\n  </div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/common\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/common\n - api/common/FormatWidth\n - api/common/NgLocaleLocalization#locale\n - api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat#description\n - api/common/getLocaleDateTimeFormat#getlocaledatetimeformat\n - api/core/Version#full\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts?message=docs(common)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L283-L313\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.1.0/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts#L283-L313\n-->"
